==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tribunal
<hw>Tri*bu"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tribunal</ets>, fr. <ets>tribunus</ets> a tribune who administered
justice: cf. F. <ets>tribunal</ets>. See <er>Tribune</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The seat of a judge; the bench on which a judge and his
associates sit for administering justice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a court or forum; <as>as, the House of Lords,
in England, is the highest <ex>tribunal</ex> in the
kingdom</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tribunal</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tribunal
<hw>Tri`bu*nal"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<def>In villages of the Philippine Islands, a kind of townhall. At the
tribunal the head men of the village met to transact business, prisoners
were confined, and troops and travelers were often quartered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tribunary</ent>⟦br⟧
